{cursor}

// Infographic - Comparison Chart
A split-screen comparison chart with two items placed symmetrically on either side of a thin vertical divider. The two item names supplied by the user are rendered as bold headers at the top of each half. Beneath each, a large illustration of the item, followed by a row-aligned attribute list with matching values/icons on both sides so readers can compare line by line. Restrained modern palette, plenty of whitespace, clean sans-serif typography. Editorial magazine layout quality.

Negative Prompt:
gibberish text, single subject, cluttered, blurry, low quality, watermark, logo

