Black-and-white film noir photograph in the 1940s Hollywood tradition. Stark high-contrast chiaroscuro lighting from a single hard directional source, deep impenetrable blacks and bright specular highlights with minimal midtones. Venetian-blind shadow patterns cutting across the subject. Vintage grain, mysterious atmosphere, hardboiled-detective mood. No color anywhere, pure silver-gelatin monochrome feel.

